amily: Aptos, sans-serif;"><u><span style=3D"">Standard of reinstatement</sp=
an></u><span style=3D""><br></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(33, 33, 33);">I=
 believe that the policy requires that&nbsp;repairs must reinstate affected p=
arts to a standard reasonably equivalent to when new (appearance, size, func=
tionality, integrity, relative quality). For visible finishes such as brickw=
ork, replacements should match identically in appearance and quality, so the=
 final result is indistinguishable and durable.</span><span style=3D"font-si=
ze: 12pt; color: rgb(33, 33, 33);"><o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"mar=
gin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><u><span style=3D=
"">Building consent &amp; AC2213</span></u><span style=3D""><br>ASURNZ=E2=80=
=99s narrative suggests no consent under Schedule 1/s42A. My understanding i=
